data.details: On March 12, 1912, Juliette Low started something for the girls of Savannah and America and all the world. Wouldn’t you like to journey to Savannah where it all began? Travel by chartered bus to Savannah and visit the Birthplace of Girl Scouts and First Headquarters take a Trolley tour, visit Tybee Island to see the lighthouse and museum, and stop at Old Fort Jackson, among other places. Join us!
